 &lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Galleries</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/galleries/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/galleries/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If there are some images stored as resources for given page, theme will render
interactive image gallery at the bottom of the page. This example also
demonstrate how to use resources metadata to describe and order images.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The params for the single image can contain following parameters:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;params.weight&lt;/code&gt; - (optional) number which specify order of the image. Lower values will sort
images to the beginning. The weight could be negative and must be quoted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;params.featured&lt;/code&gt; - (optional) true/false value to specify that given image
will be used on higher levels (e.g. in list of blog posts) to represent the
current page/post.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;params.gallery&lt;/code&gt; - (optional) number which specifies which gallery image
belongs to. This brings possibility to group images into multiple galleries.
&lt;strong&gt;Gallery with index 0&lt;/strong&gt; has special meaning - image will be hidden.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Images In Single Post</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/images_in_single_post/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/images_in_single_post/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is page shows how to insert single images into content text. There are
multiple ways - via makrdown notation or hugo keyword &lt;code&gt;figure&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="disable-gallery"&gt;Disable gallery&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you decide to insert images (stored in a subdirectory of the post) manually
to the text, it could be handy to disable disable automatic generated image gallery at the bottom
of the page. This can be configured in page front matter - the boolean attribute &lt;code&gt;hide_gallery&lt;/code&gt;. Setting
the value to &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt; will disable gallery&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Last Modified Sidebar</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/last_modified_sidebar/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/last_modified_sidebar/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;You can configure your site to show list of last 10 modified or created pages. The date
is taken from file system or from your local git repository.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To switch the side bar on, extend configuration of your site (&lt;code&gt;config.yaml&lt;/code&gt; in root folder
of your site) of the parameter &lt;code&gt;showLastModifiedSidebar&lt;/code&gt; and set it to &lt;code&gt;yes&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;params&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;author&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;Wanderer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;poweredBy&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;Powered by &amp;lt;a href=&amp;#39;http://www.gohugo.io/&amp;#39;&amp;gt;Hugo&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;showLastModified&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;yes&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to use dates from github repository, add also this configuration:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Map With Tags</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/map-tags/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/map-tags/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;No content shown here is rendered, all content is based in the appropriate template&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Setting a very low sitemap priority will tell search engines this is not important content.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Map With Tags And Tracks</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/map/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/map/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;No content shown here is rendered, all content is based in the appropriate template&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Setting a very low sitemap priority will tell search engines this is not important content.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Maps</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/maps/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/maps/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If there is at least one gpx file in resources of given page, it will be
automatically rendered at the bottom of the page, including basic legend with
distance, time and possibility to download individual gpx files. If the gpx
file contains waypoints, all will be rendered with appropriate icons (see next
chapters).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="waypoints-and-icons"&gt;Waypoints and Icons&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The gpx file can contain both tracks and waypoints (POI - points of interest). Current version
of the template supports following symbols (icons):&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Markdown</title><link>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/markdown/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mnezerka.github.io/wanderer/features/markdown/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is an overview of various markdown elemens to see wanderer rendering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="lists"&gt;Lists&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simple list:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;first item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;second item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;third item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nested list:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;first item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;second item
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;first sub item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;second sub item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;third sub item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
